{\bf Robustness assumption * : }
A plausibility space with a partial order relation on the domain of plausibility values , describing the relation ' more plausible than ' , is definable using indexed sets of plausibility spaces each having a linearly ordered domain of plausibility values .
In such a space , an event $e_1$ is more plausible than $e_2$ if and only if it is more plausible in each constituent indexed space .

